  "prompt": "Can I use any image from google/website in my blog, along with mentioning the credits for the image?",
  "response": "No, simply crediting an image does not automatically give you permission to use it. Using images from Google or websites without explicit permission can potentially infringe on copyright. Here are some legal ways to use images:\n\n1. Use images with a Creative Commons license\n2. Purchase stock photos from websites like Shutterstock\n3. Use images from free stock photo sites like:\n- Unsplash\n- Pixabay\n- Pexels\n- Canva free images\n\n4. Get direct permission from the copyright owner\n5. Use images you've created yourself\n6. Use images with an open-source or public domain license\n\nAlways check the specific licensing terms before using any image. Some key steps:\n- Look for usage rights\n- Verify if commercial use is allowed\n- Check if attribution is required\n- Confirm the license matches your intended use\n\nIf you're unsure, it's safest to:\n- Contact the image creator\n- Purchase a license\n- Create or commission your own images\n\nRemember: Copyright infringement can lead to legal issues, takedown notices, or financial penalties, so it's important to be cautious and respectful of intellectual property rights.",
